    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "1.1 Select geographical area (districts and villages) for focus of Project work\r\n\r\n1.2 Prepare and conduct inception workshop for the launching of the Project\r\n\r\n1.3 Conduct base line studies within the first four months of the Project inception and share the results\r\n\r\n1.4 Conduct final workshop to share results and lessons learned\r\n\r\n2.1 Pilot test best bet agroforestry options and enterprises in the selected farm households’ underutilised/ abandoned agricultural land\r\n\r\n2.2 Publish and share  Project results (main findings, experiences, conclusion and recommendations)\r\n\r\n3.1 Prepare a National Action Plan for the utilization of underutilized/ abandoned agricultural land\r\n\r\n3.2 Formulate a project proposal to support the GON in scaling up of the Pilot Project results across the country\r\n\r\n4.1 Plan and carry out awareness raising activities on the underutilized / abandoned agri. land for target audiences and the general public\r\n\r\n4.2 Conduct Capacity Building Need Assessment of farm households, govt. and non-govt organizations, authorities responsible for tenurial issues and business entrepreneurs\r\n\r\n4.3 Develop capacity building materials\r\n\r\n4.4 Organize and conduct Training of Trainers (ToT) for the people who will be involved in the capacity building of the farm households in the Project districts\r\n\r\n4.5 Plan and execute capacity building activities of farm households in the Project pilot sites\r\n\r\n4.6 Document key Project learning, experiences and results and communicate widely to people within and outside the Project districts across Nepal and beyond."
      },
      "ne": null
    },
